						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near the northern gateway leading to the Tuṅgabhadrā river in the Pampāpati temple.<note n="44-3">The text of the record is not available.</note></p>						

						<p>Sōmēśvara, 1236 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged and worn out record, both in Sanskrit and Kannaḍa, registers a royal gift of money-income to the temple of Virūpākshadēva for worship and feeding the <hi rend="italic">brāhmaṇas</hi> in the <hi rend="italic">sattra</hi> attached thereto.</p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1159, Durmukhi, Pushya ba. 11, Thursday, Uttarāyaṇa-saṁkrānti</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1236 A.D., December 25.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
